
@startuml

' Entities
class Person {
  - personID: String
  - name: String
  - phoneNumber: String
  - keywords: List<String>
  - institutionCode: String
}

class Institution {
  - institutionCode: String
  - name: String
}

class Article {
  - doi: String
  - title: String
  - authors: List<Person>
  - authorPositions: List<Integer>
}

class PeerReviewedPaper {
  - citationCount: Integer
  - reviewers: List<Person>
}

class TechnicalReport {
  - publisherInstitutionCode: String
}

class Publisher {
  - name: String
}

class Journal {
  - name: String
  - impactFactor: Double
  - publisherName: String
}

class Subscription {
  - institutionCode: String
  - journalName: String
  - publisherName: String
}

' Relationships
Person "1" -- "0..*" Article : writes as author
Person "1" -- "0..*" Article : reviews

Article "1" -- "1" PeerReviewedPaper : is a
Article "1" -- "1" TechnicalReport : is a

PeerReviewedPaper "1" -- "0..*" Person : reviewed by

TechnicalReport "1" -- "1" Institution : published by

Publisher "1" -- "0..*" Journal : publishes

Journal "1" -- "0..*" Subscription : has subscribers

Institution "1" -- "0..*" Subscription : subscribes to

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Person**:
  - Identified by `personID`.
  - Works at an **Institution**.
  - Can be both **author** and **reviewer** of different **Articles**.

- **Institution**:
  - Identified by `institutionCode`.
  - Publishes **TechnicalReports** and subscribes to **Journals**.

- **Article**:
  - Base class with common properties (`doi`, `title`, `authors`).
  - Inherited by `PeerReviewedPaper` and `TechnicalReport`.

- **PeerReviewedPaper**:
  - Has a `citationCount` and a list of `reviewers`.

- **TechnicalReport**:
  - Always published by a single **Institution**.

- **Publisher**:
  - Identified by name.
  - Publishes multiple **Journals** (which may have the same name as other publishers).

- **Journal**:
  - Has a `name`, `impactFactor`, and associated `publisherName`.

- **Subscription**:
  - Represents an **Institution**'s subscription to a **Journal** from a **Publisher**.

---

